Quick Brainstorm: Possible Main Goals (\u8220\'93What am I actually trying to do?\u8221\'94)Since you start as a freshly built/activated robot in an engineering lab with Calethina, here are some strong directional ideas that fit the \u8220\'93Fallout New Vegas \u215\'d7 Cyberpunk in Antarctica\u8221\'94 tone. We can mix, modify, or replace them:A. The Signal / The Tower\line You discover (or are tasked by Calethina) that Amundsen Tower\u8217\'92s space elevator is showing faint reactivation signs. Your long-term goal: reach the Tower, repair/reactivate it, and either call down help from the off-world Tepenians or decide whether humanity/robots on Earth deserve rescue. Moral weight: some factions want to keep everyone grounded, others want to escape at any cost.B. Rebuilding Tepenia\line You are a \u8220\'93Bridge Unit\u8221\'94 \u8212\'97 a rare new robot model designed to literally bridge the divide between remaining humans and robots. Goal: unify (or choose a side in) Concordia\u8217\'92s fractured society and turn the city into a viable new nation. Involves faction quests, big reputation decisions, and multiple endings.C. The Memory Hunt\line As a new robot, you start with fragmented or implanted memories. Goal: piece together what really happened during the Midnight War and why certain robots/humans were left behind. Leads to conspiracies, hidden bunkers under Concordia, and confronting the truth about the Falkland Treaty.D. Calethina\u8217\'92s Secret\line Calethina is not just a helpful AI \u8212\'97 she has her own agenda (maybe she\u8217\'92s the last fragment of a greater mind, or she\u8217\'92s dying, or she needs you to finish something she started before the evacuation). Your personal goal evolves from \u8220\'93survive in Concordia\u8221\'94 to fulfilling (or betraying) her vision.Hybrid approach (my favorite for your style):\line Start small \u8212\'97 \u8220\'93find a stable power source / secure the lab\u8221\'94 \u8212\'97 then naturally open up into one of the bigger goals above based on player choices.Would you like me to expand any of these, or do you already have a gut feeling toward one direction?}
