The Siligel Crisis\line The lab\u8217\'92s emergency siligel reserves are contaminated or depleted. Calethina tasks you with securing a stable supply for the immediate district before the local robots (and their human partners) begin to shut down. First choice: raid an old stockpile, negotiate with a faction, or improvise a substitute (with side effects).}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  2.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Heating Grid Failure\line A critical heating main has ruptured under the district. You have a narrow window to reroute power/heat before dozens of hab-blocks freeze. This introduces resource trade-offs immediately (divert from hydroponics? from Arcanet servers? from manufacturing?).}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  3.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Calethina\u8217\'92s Failing Core\line Calethina herself is degrading (holographic glitches, memory corruption). Your first task is to locate and retrieve a specific rare component or data shard inside Concordia that can stabilize her. She can only guide you for so long\u8230\'85}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  4.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The First Bridge Test\line Calethina activates you specifically to mediate an emerging dispute between two local factions who are about to come to blows over a shared resource depot. Your success (or failure) in diplomacy sets your reputation tone for the entire game.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  5.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Missing Data Core\line A vital Arcanet node containing pre-war survival schematics has gone offline. Retrieve it before the knowledge is lost forever \u8212\'97 but factions already have competing claims on the area.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  6.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Orphaned Unit\line A previous experimental robot (your \u8220\'93sibling\u8221\'94) went missing shortly after activation. Find them before they cause (or suffer) irreversible damage.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  7.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Hydroponic Collapse\line One of the district\u8217\'92s main food production facilities is failing. Secure replacement parts or expertise before the human population faces starvation.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  8.\tab}\ilvl0\ls41 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Ossuary Request (more atmospheric)\line The Goth community asks Calethina for a new Bridge Unit to help consecrate a new wing of the Ossuary using fallen robots\u8217\'92 parts. Your first mission is to retrieve specific \u8220\'93bones\u8221\'94 (chassis remnants) while learning about death, memory, and legacy.}
\par \pard\plain \s22\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Act 3 + Climax / Final Confrontation IdeasBy Act 3 the player has built deep relationships, made many painful choices, and accumulated a lot of reputation (and enemies). The climax should feel like a direct consequence of everything you\u8217\'92ve done.Here are 7 possible end-game scenarios (all inside Concordia):}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  1.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Great Blackout\line A cascading failure threatens to plunge the entire city into darkness and lethal cold. You must decide how to redistribute the last remaining power. Multiple factions storm the Central Thermal Spire for control. The \u8220\'93final battle\u8221\'94 is a large tactical siege/combat inside the spire where former allies may turn on you depending on past choices.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  2.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Arcanet Singularity\line The city\u8217\'92s Arcanet core has become unstable from all the patched-in data shards. It begins rewriting reality (glitching robots, false memories, holographic ghosts). You enter the massive data-vault for a psychological/moral climax where you confront digital versions of people you\u8217\'92ve harmed or helped.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  3.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Succession Crisis\line Calethina\u8217\'92s degradation reaches a breaking point. Several factions want to claim her remaining processing power or install their own AI successor. The climax is a multi-faction summit/confrontation in the old Central Dome where you choose who (or what) will guide Concordia\u8217\'92s future.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  4.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Siligel Wars\line A massive shortage turns philosophical disagreements violent. Different districts begin hoarding or raiding. You must choose which community to save at the expense of others, culminating in a tragic battle in the central refinery district.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  5.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Ossuary Awakening\line The Goths\u8217\'92 accumulated \u8220\'93metal bones\u8221\'94 in the Ossuary begin to reactivate (corrupted war memories or a new emergent intelligence). The climax takes place inside the haunting cathedral as you decide whether to let the dead rest, weaponize them, or merge with them.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  6.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Bridge Overload\line You (the player) have become too influential. Multiple factions simultaneously try to either upload you into the Solarnet, dismantle you for parts, or worship you as the new guiding intelligence. The final sequence is a personal, introspective confrontation mixed with tactical defense of your own chassis.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain  7.\tab}\ilvl0\ls42 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
The Long Night Returns\line Sensors detect a new, smaller-scale \u8220\'93Midnight War\u8221\'94 event approaching (solar flare, tectonic instability, or resource panic). The climax is a desperate, city-wide effort to survive one final night \u8212\'97 every past choice determines which districts stand with you when the lights start going out.}
