\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
in terms of reputation, I'd like to base it on the system used in Fallout: New Vegas. That being, that it's possible to have both positive and negative reputation with the same faction. Like, for example, simultaneously having both "Idolized" and "Vilified" status with a faction results in having what Fallout New Vegas calles "Wild Child" status. I want to use something like that.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
