\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Perfect \u8212\'97 we'll base the reputation system directly on the Fallout: New Vegas model. This fits Inner Tepenia extremely well because it naturally supports painful trade-offs: you can do great things for a faction (build Fame) while still committing acts that harm them or their priorities (gain Infamy), leading to complex, mixed relationships.Core Reputation Mechanics (F:NV-Inspired)Each faction tracks two separate values:}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls71 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Fame (Positive reputation) \u8212\'97 Earned by helping them, completing their quests, aligning with their philosophy.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af6 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\f6\dbch\af6 \u57352\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls71 \fi-283\li0\lin0\tx709\fi-283\li709\lin709\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Infamy (Negative reputation) \u8212\'97 Gained by harming their interests, diverting resources away from them, causing indirect suffering, or being caught in conflicting actions.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
These two values do not cancel each other out. They combine into an overall title/status that determines how the faction treats you (dialogue, discounts, quest access, hostility, etc.).Example Status Grid (Adapted for Tepenia)We'll use a clean 4\u215\'d74 or 5\u215\'d75 matrix similar to New Vegas:}
