\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\aspalpha\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\ql\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\aspalpha\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
I'd like to set things in such a way that Calethina's lab is not the only functional robot-engineering laboratory. There are several of them scattered across the city. It's just that many more of them have had to be temporarily shut down due to energy concerns. The reason for this is because I don't want for any faction to be automatically "hostile" towards the player right from the beginning, as it would limit roleplaying freedom. Like, say for example, the player wants to roleplay as a robot who's loyal to districts such as Hearthward, Havenward, or Frostward. If those districts are already hostile towards the player right from the beginning, it would limit roleplaying freedom. Are there any ways to account for this, while still providing a compelling early-game narrative hook?}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af9\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\widctlpar\hyphpar0\aspalpha\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1033\kerning1\dbch\af10\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
Yes \u8212\'97 this is a very smart and important concern. We can absolutely preserve maximum roleplaying freedom while keeping a strong, compelling early-game hook.Here\u8217\'92s how we can elegantly solve it:Core PrincipleNo faction starts hostile toward you.\line At worst, some factions are wary, frustrated, or politically opposed to the fact that Calethina\u8217\'92s lab (in the Forgeward) is still running at full power while theirs are shut down. But this frustration is aimed at the situation and the resource allocation, not at you personally as a newly activated Bridge Unit.You begin with a clean reputation slate across the board (Neutral or slightly positive with a couple of factions).}
\par \pard\plain \s22\rtlch\afs12 \ltrch\loch\sb0\sa283\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrdb\brdrw1\brdrcf15\brsp0\brdrr\brdrnone\noline\fs12\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s18\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\ltrpar{\hich\af4\loch\cf1\f4\loch
